hage |publisher=Penguin (original ed.:Robert Hale 1960) |ref=harv }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* Carayon, Nicolas, ''[http://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/docs/00/28/32/10/PDF/3vol.pdf Les ports ph\u00e9niciens et puniques]'', PhD Thesis, 2008, Strasbourg, France.\n* Cerqueiro, Daniel, ''{{lang|es|Las Naves de Tarshis o qui\u00e9nes fueron los Fenicios}}'', Buenos Aires, Ed. Peq. Venecia, 2002, {{ISBN|987-9239-13-X}}.\n* Cioffi, Robert L., \"A Palm Tree, a Colour and a Mythical Bird\" (review of Josephine Quinn, ''In Search of the Phoenicians'', Princeton, 2017, 360 pp., {{ISBN|978 0 691 17527 0}}), ''[[London Review of Books]]'', vol. 41, no. 1 (3 January 2019), pp. 15\u201316.\n* [[George Rawlinson|Rawlinson, George]], ''The History of Phoenicia'', 1889, available [http://digital.library.upenn.edu/webbin/gutbook/lookup?num=2331 online] under [[Project Gutenberg]]. Rawlinson's 19th-century text needs updating for modern improvements in historical understanding.\n* [[Jean-Pierre Thiollet|Thiollet, Jean-Pierre]], ''{{lang|fr|Je m'appelle Byblos}}'', foreword by Guy Gay-Para, H & D, Paris, 2005, {{ISBN|2-914266-04-9}}.\n* {{cite book |last=Todd |first=Malcolm |authorlink=Malcolm Todd |author2=Andrew Fleming |title=The South West to AD 1,000 (Regional history of England series No.:8) |publisher=Longman |location=Harlow, Essex |year=1987 |isbn=978-0-582-49274-5 }}, for a critical examination of the evidence of Phoenician trade with the South West of the U.K.\n* Silva, Di\u00f3genes. \"La literatura sobre fenicios en el territorio brasile\u00f1o: or\u00edgenes y razones\", PhD Thesis, Madrid - 2016. Available in https://eprints.ucm.es/39468/\n\n== External links ==\n{{Library resources box |by=no |onlinebooks=yes |others=yes |about=yes |label=Phoenicia\n |viaf= |lccn= |lcheading= |wikititle= }}\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03szw8l BBC Radio4 \u2013 In Our Time: The Phoenicians (audio archive)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090110073346/http://www.nowlebanon.com/NewsArticleDetails.aspx?ID=69741&MID=123&PID=2 The quest for the Phoenicians in South Lebanon]\n* [https://www.omniglot.com/writing/phoenician.htm Phoenician Alphabet]\n* {{cite web|url=https://aeon.co/essays/phoenicia-an-imaginary-friend-to-nations-in-need-of-ancestors|title=Phoenicia: An imaginary friend to nations in need of ancestors|work=Josephine Quinn, associate professor in ancient history at Worcester College, [[University of Oxford]]|editor=Sam Haselby|publisher=Aeon}}\n\n{{Ancient states and regions of the Levant |state=collapsed}}\n{{Ancient Syria and Mesopotamia}}\n{{Phoenician cities and colonies navbox}}\n{{Empires}}\n{{Subject bar |commons=y|wikt=y|s=y }}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Phoenicia| ]]\n[[Category:Ancient Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Ancient Levant]]\n[[Category:Ancient Near East]]\n[[Category:Bronze Age Asia]]\n[[Category:Bronze Age cultures]]\n[[Category:Iron Age cultures of Asia]]\n[[Category:Iron Age cultures of Africa]]\n[[Category:History of the Mediterranean]]\n[[Category:Ancient Asia]]\n[[Category:Ancient Africa]]\n[[Category:Ancient Europe]]\n[[Category:Ancient Syria]]\n[[Category:Ancient history of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Ancient history of the Iberian Peninsula]]\n[[Category:Ancient history of North Africa]]\n[[Category:History of Palestine (region)]]\n[[Category:History of Western Asia]]\n[[Category:Civilizations]]\n[[Category:2nd millennium BC]]\n[[Category:9th century BC]]\n[[Category:8th century BC]]\n[[Category:7th century BC]]\n[[Category:6th century BC]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in the 16th century BC]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in the 6th century BC]]\n[[Category:12th-century BC establishments]]\n[[Category:6th-century BC disestablishments]]\n", "name_user": "Ira Leviton", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted a duplicate \"the\".", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoenicia"}
{"title_page": "Thant Sin Maung", "text_new": "{{short description|Burmese politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix =[[His Excellency]] \n|name        = Thant Sin Maung\n|honorific-suffix = \n|native_name = {{my|\u101e\u1014\u1037\u103a\u1005\u1004\u103a\u1019\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a}}\n|native_name_lang = Burmese\n|image       =\n|alt         = \n|caption     = \n|office =  [[Ministry of Transport and Communications (Myanmar)|Minister for Transport and Communications]]\n|president = [[Htin Kyaw]]<br />[[Myint Swe (general)|Myint Swe]] (acting)<br />[[Win Myint (politician, born 1951)|Win Myint]]\n|term_start = 30 March 2016\n|term_end  = \n|predecessor = [[Nyan Tun Aung]] (Transport)<br />[[Zayar Aung]] (Communication) \n|successor =\n|succeeding = \n|office1 =  [[Pyithu Hluttaw]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n|constituency1 = [[Monywa Township]] \n|majority1 = \n|term_start1  = 1 February 2016\n|term_end1    = 30 March 2016\n|predecessor1 = \n|successor1   =Nyunt Aung \n| party = [[National League for Democracy]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1953|11|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Monywa Township]], [[Sagaing Division]], [[Burma]] (Myanmar)\n| death_date  = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| residence   = [[Hlaing Township]], [[Yangon]]\n| nationality = Burmese\n| ethnicity   = \n| occupation  = Academic, Government Servant, Politician\n| spouse      = Khin Than Aye\n| children    = 3\n| relations   = \n| alma_mater = [[Yangon University]]\n| website     = \n}}\n'''Thant Sin Maung''' ({{lang-my|\u101e\u1014\u1037\u103a\u1005\u1004\u103a\u1019\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a}} {{IPA-my|\u03b8a\u0330\u0274 s\u026a\u0300\u0274 m\u00e0\u028a\u0274|}}; born 15 November 1953) is a [[Myanmar|Burmese]] politician and incumbent [[Ministry of Transport and Communications (Myanmar)|Minister for Transport and Communications]] of [[Myanmar]] (Burma). On 22 March 2016, he was nominated to be Minister for Transport and Communications in [[President of Myanmar|President]] [[Htin Kyaw]]'s [[First Htin Kyaw's Cabinet|Cabinet]]. On 24 March, the [[Assembly of the Union]] confirmed his nomination.\n\nHe previously served as [[Pyithu Hluttaw]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Monywa Township]].<ref name=\"themyanmartimes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/19591-daw-aung-san-suu-kyi-to-join-government-as-nld-reveals-cabinet.html|title=Daw Aung San Suu Kyi to join government as NLD reveals cabinet|author=The Myanmar Times|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/nay-pyi-taw/19571-with-all-eyes-on-daw-suu-nld-set-to-reveal-cabinet.html|title=With all eyes on Daw Suu, NLD set to reveal cabinet|author=Ei Ei Toe Lwin|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"WMA\">{{cite web | url=http://app.mvoter2015.com/candidate/a5071d0171954b8dcacd2f2ba70f937a | title=\u1026\u1038\u101e\u1014\u1037\u103a\u1005\u1004\u103a\u1019\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a  \u1021\u1019\u103b\u102d\u102f\u1038\u101e\u102c\u1038\u1012\u102e\u1019\u102d\u102f\u1000\u101b\u1031\u1005\u102e\u1021\u1016\u103d\u1032\u1037\u1001\u103b\u102f\u1015\u103a\u1015\u102b\u1010\u102e | work=mVoter2015 | accessdate=26 March 2016 }}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref><ref name=\"7Day\" />\n\n== Early life and education==\nThant Sin Maung was born on 15 November 1953 in Monyway village, [[Monywa Township]], [[Sagaing Division]], [[Burma]] (now Myanmar) to Lu Lay and Ohn Kyi.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/7daynews/posts/1117673254960974|title=\u1015\u103c\u100a\u103a\u1011\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a\u1005\u102f\u101d\u1014\u103a\u1000\u103c\u102e\u1038\u1019\u103b\u102c\u1038\u104f\u1000\u102d\u102f\u101a\u103a\u101b\u1031\u1038\u1021\u1000\u103b\u1009\u103a\u1038\u1019\u103b\u102c|last=|first=|date=|website=7Day News Journal|language=|lang=my|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> He graduated from [[Yangon University|Rangoon Arts and Science University]] with [[M.Sc.]] in [[Mathematics]].<ref name=\"7Day\" />\n==Governmental career==\nThant Zin Maung started working as a tutor in Pathein College and Rangoon Arts and Science University. He then moved to [[Myanmar Railways]] as an assistant manager, and worked in various positions until his retirement as a general manager.<ref name=\"7Day\">{{cite web | url=http://www.7daydaily.com/story/60965 | title=\u1015\u103c\u100a\u103a\u1011\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a\u1005\u102f\u101d\u1014\u103a\u1000\u103c\u102e\u1038\u101e\u1005\u103a\u1019\u103b\u102c\u1038\u104f \u1000\u102d\u102f\u101a\u103a\u101b\u1031\u1038\u1021\u1000\u103b\u1009\u103a\u1038\u1019\u103b\u102c\u1038 | work=[[7Day News]] | date=22 March 2016 | accessdate=26 March 2016 | language=Burmese}}</ref>\n\n== Political career ==\nIn [[2015 Myanmar general election]], he was elected as a [[Pyithu Hluttaw]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Monywa Township]].<ref name=\"7Day\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nHe married to Khin Than Aye, a medical [[Physician|doctor]], and has three children, Arkar Thant Sin, Phu Thant Sin, and Htoo Thant Sin.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"7Day\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thant Sin Maung}}\n[[Category:Government ministers of Myanmar]]\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sagaing Region]]\n[[Category:National League for Democracy politicians]]\n[[Category:University of Yangon alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the House of Representatives (Burma)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Burmese politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix =[[His Excellency]] \n|name        = Thant Sin Maung\n|honorific-suffix = \n|native_name = {{my|\u101e\u1014\u1037\u103a\u1005\u1004\u103a\u1019\u1031\u102c\u1004\u103a}}\n|native_name_lang = Burmese\n|image       =\n|alt         = \n|caption     = \n|office =  [[Ministry of Transport and Communicatio